The President is urging Congress to take action on immigration reform and address the issue of the 11 million undocumented immigrants in the country. He notes that both Republicans and Democrats seem willing to work together on this issue, with bipartisan groups actively working on a solution. The President is encouraged by the recent announcement of principles for comprehensive immigration reform by a bipartisan group of Senators, which align with his own proposed principles. He expresses hope that progress will be made soon.